# Line endings for cross-platform (esp. Windows) checkouts.
# Text/source defaults to LF — Windows otherwise checks out CRLF, which adds \r to
# the heredoc-based spec fixtures (spec/table/*) and fails the suite.
* text=auto eol=lf
# Batch files MUST stay CRLF — cmd.exe mis-parses LF-only .bat/.cmd (breaks
# setup.bat / tools/win-build.bat: REM lines run as commands, if/else falls through).
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.cmd text eol=crlf
# Binary assets: never normalize.
*.png binary
*.ico binary
*.ttf binary
